# Spark UI — reading the tabs

After localising the slow **task** — three tabs.

- **Jobs** — row per action · **Stages** — row per stage (work between shuffles) → click in
- **Stage detail** — Tasks table + **task summary metrics** (min/median/max)

| Signal | Diagnosis |
|---|---|
| Max duration ≫ median | **skew** |
| Huge total shuffle write | **shuffle-heavy** |
| Spill > 0 | **memory pressure** |
| GC = big fraction of task | memory pressure / OOM soon |
| Many tasks < 100 ms | **over-fragmentation** |

- **Executors tab** — per-executor memory/disk; dead executor → **OOM**

**Read max-vs-median first:** skew (max≫median) vs. uniformly heavy — different fixes.
